1. *Ne laži* mi, znam da si ti ukrao moj telefon. (Don't lie to me, I know you stole my phone.)
2. Oni *lagu* da su bili na putovanju, ali ja znam da su zapravo bili kod kuće. (They are lying that they went on a trip, but I know they were actually at home.)
3. Kada sam videla da su mi pare nestale, nisam mogla da verujem da me je moj najbolji prijatelj *prevario* i *lagao*. (When I saw that my money was gone, I couldn't believe that my best friend had cheated and lied to me.)
4. Da li ti ikada *laziš* u vezi svojih osećanja? (Do you ever lie about your feelings?)
5. Često *lazem* roditeljima da sam u biblioteci kada sam zapravo u kafiću. (I often lie to my parents that I'm at the library when I'm actually at a cafe.)
6. Nije u redu *lagati* ljude samo da bi se izvukao iz problema. (It's not right to lie to people just to get out of trouble.)
7. Moja baka voli da *lazi* svojim unucima priče o njenom detinjstvu. (My grandma likes to tell her grandchildren stories about her childhood that are not true.)
8. Kada su me pitali da li sam videla ko je ukrao novac iz kase, morala sam da *lagem* jer sam znala da je to moj brat. (When they asked me if I had seen who stole the money from the cash register, I had to lie because I knew it was my brother.)